        <section name="Quick Start">
            <p>
                First,
                <a href="download">download</a>
                StatCVS.
            </p>

            <p>
                Check out a working copy of your project from CVS. You need the CVS command line client (CVS for Unix or
                <a href="http://www.cvsnt.org/">CVSNT</a>
                for Windows). Typically, the command looks like this:
            </p>
            <pre>cvs -d /cvsroot checkout modulename</pre>

            <p>Create a CVS log file:</p>
            <pre>cvs log > logfile.log</pre>

            <p>Run StatCVS:</p>
            <pre>java -jar /path/to/statcvs.jar /path/to/module/logfile.log /path/to/module</pre>
            <p>This command creates the HTML reports in the current directory.</p>
            <p>
                More details are available from the
                <a href="manual">Manual</a>
                . It also has all the options for customizing the reports. If you run into problems, consider asking for help on the
                <a href="mailto:statcvs-users@lists.sourceforge.net">statcvs-users Mailing list</a>
                .
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Note:</strong>
                StatCVS can only generate reports for the main branch.
            </p>
        </section>


